There have now been seven Covid-19 deaths recorded in South Africa, health minister Dr Zweli Mkhize said on Friday. Speaking in Cape Town, he said there were now 1,505 cases of Covid-19 recorded across the country, an increase of 43 from Thursday night. Mkhize said the two new recorded deaths were an 80-year-old man and an 81-year-old woman in KwaZulu-Natal. This is a developing story.